1
00:01:01,700 --> 00:01:04,400
<i>This was the house
I used to dream of.</i>

2
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,433
<i>I thought this was where
we'd build a happy family</i>

3
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:12,700
<i> and beautiful memories.</i>

4
00:01:12,833 --> 00:01:14,833
Marj, wait. Marj!

5
00:01:14,967 --> 00:01:16,133
Marj, stop!

6
00:01:16,267 --> 00:01:21,033
<i>But as it burns and fills
the air with thick smoke...</i>

7
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:26,900
<i>it's like all its dark secrets
are coming out.</i>

8
00:01:27,033 --> 00:01:31,000
You promised me a whole,
happy family!

9
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:34,533
But you're the one
who destroyed us!

10
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:37,633
<i> You can't escape tragedy.</i>

11
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:38,833
<i> Everyone gets dragged into it.</i>

12
00:01:38,967 --> 00:01:41,600
No brother would ever do that
to his own brother!

13
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:43,367
<i> Everything you care about,</i>

14
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:46,633
<i>everything you've protected
for so long...</i>

15
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:50,067
<i> will be gone in an instant.</i>

16
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,200
Don't ever go against
your big brother.

17
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:55,633
Unless you want trouble.

18
00:01:55,767 --> 00:01:58,100
For once, just be fair!

19
00:01:58,233 --> 00:02:00,267
<i> When your world falls apart,</i>

20
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:03,467
<i>that's when you find out
who's really on your side...</i>

21
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:05,433
Stop pretending!

22
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:07,067
I know the truth!

23
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:09,633
<i> and who ruined your life.</i>

24
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:11,400
Don't drag me into your mess!

25
00:02:11,533 --> 00:02:13,333
You're the one causing all this!

26
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:35,767
<i>I thought the home I entered was
strong, happy, and perfect.</i>

27
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:40,267
<i> But it was all an illusion.</i>

28
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:43,867
<i>This house wasn't built
on stone...</i>

29
00:02:46,433 --> 00:02:49,067
<i> it was built on lies.</i>

30
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,300
And the award

31
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:57,533
for Most Outstanding Real Estate
Agent goes to...

32
00:03:59,767 --> 00:04:01,900
Marjorie Castillo.

33
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:11,633
Congratulations.

34
00:04:11,767 --> 00:04:13,467
Thank you so much.

35
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:22,700
Thank you, everyone.

36
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,833
There was a time

37
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,467
when my mom, my sibling,
and I slept on the streets.

38
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:35,433
So when we left Cebu
and moved here to Batangas,

39
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,267
I promised them

40
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:43,800
I'd give them a better life
and a home of our own.

41
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,767
I really love this job.

42
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:57,733
Every time I see my clients
finally get their dream house,

43
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:00,567
it gives me hope

44
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,300
that through hard work
and perseverance,

45
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:04,633
my own dream
will also come true.

46
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,400
So let's keep fighting
for our dreams.

47
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,767
That's the end of the program.

48
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,533
Enjoy the rest
of the celebration.

49
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:32,133
You were amazing!

50
00:05:33,400 --> 00:05:35,933
- Congrats!
- Congratulations, babe.

51
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:37,633
I'm so proud of you.

52
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:39,767
Since you're my girlfriend,
it feels like I won, too.

53
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:43,667
Wow, my boyfriend is so sweet.

54
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,533
Hey!

55
00:05:44,667 --> 00:05:45,867
Hey! You two are so sweet.

56
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,733
If there were a Love Team
of the Year, you two would win.

57
00:05:49,867 --> 00:05:50,933
So when's the wedding?

58
00:05:51,067 --> 00:05:52,800
Better save that gown for later.

59
00:05:52,933 --> 00:05:54,633
It's going to be a while.

60
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:58,033
Building the house comes first
for my babe and me.

61
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:01,533
Careful, someone might steal
Randall from you.

62
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:08,267
No way! I'm the only woman
in his life, right, babe?

63
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:10,833
Of course.

64
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:15,367
- Congratulations.
- Oh, thank you.

65
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:17,100
Let me see that!

66
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:18,033
Hey, I'll take this.

67
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:19,700
- Congrats, Marj!
- Congrats, Marj!

68
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:20,900
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

69
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:27,300
Jobert, why aren't you using
the headphones I gave you?

70
00:06:27,433 --> 00:06:29,467
Didn't you like them?

71
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:31,300
Sorry about that, babe.

72
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:35,700
He gets uncomfortable
when things change.

73
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:39,033
Too bad, that's really good.

74
00:06:39,167 --> 00:06:41,833
Actually,
Jobert doesn't like music.

75
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,733
He just wears them so he won't
hear the noise around him.

76
00:06:46,867 --> 00:06:49,533
It helps him relax.

77
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:51,467
Nice.

78
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,767
Jobert, come here.

79
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:55,200
Look, our dream house.

80
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:58,967
It's like our dream house.
It's beautiful.

81
00:06:59,100 --> 00:07:01,667
I like it, Sister.

82
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:05,900
I like the dream house.

83
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:08,900
Don't worry,
just hang on a little longer.

84
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:11,133
We'll live
in our dream house soon.

85
00:07:11,267 --> 00:07:13,767
You, Mom, and me.

86
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,433
Pong, too.

87
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:17,867
Of course, Pong's coming.

88
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,533
He's not getting left behind.

89
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:23,733
I will give you everything
you want and everything

90
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:25,633
that's good for you.

91
00:07:25,767 --> 00:07:28,733
Because I love you.

92
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:34,167
I love you, Sister.

93
00:07:37,267 --> 00:07:39,267
- Give me a hug.
- Hug.

94
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,533
Pong.

95
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:54,267
You know, dear, you're lucky.

96
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:57,400
You found a man like Randall.

97
00:07:57,533 --> 00:07:59,333
He really loves you.

98
00:08:01,067 --> 00:08:03,733
And I'm at peace knowing...

99
00:08:03,867 --> 00:08:05,967
he won't hurt you,

100
00:08:07,033 --> 00:08:08,800
that he won't leave you,

101
00:08:10,167 --> 00:08:13,100
unlike what happened
with your father and me.

102
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:15,267
Mom...

103
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,700
There, there.
That's enough.

104
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,000
Don't think about that anymore.

105
00:08:19,133 --> 00:08:20,367
I promise you,

106
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,600
I'll never leave you
when Randall and I settle down.

107
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:26,733
I won't abandon you or Jobert.

108
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:29,367
You'll be with me.

109
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:32,767
I'll make our dream come true.
We'll live a better life.

110
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,133
We can do it, Mom.

111
00:08:34,267 --> 00:08:36,767
And we don't need dad.

112
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,967
I know, Marj.

113
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,433
Thank you.

114
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:54,633
Hey! Everyone!

115
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,933
Come this way!

116
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,733
Stop the demolition crew!

117
00:08:57,867 --> 00:08:58,900
Come on, move!

118
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:00,633
Hurry!

119
00:09:00,767 --> 00:09:01,733
We're here.

120
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,367
Here, Sir.
Thank you.

121
00:09:18,067 --> 00:09:19,467
They told us to pass through
the back.

122
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,433
The front road's blocked.

123
00:09:21,567 --> 00:09:23,667
All right,
get some rest, Babe.

124
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:24,967
Bye.

125
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,533
Wait.

126
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:29,367
Hold on.

127
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:30,900
Oh my god. What's happening?

128
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:32,100
Why are they running?

129
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:34,533
They said there's a demolition,
Marj.

130
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:36,300
What?

131
00:09:36,433 --> 00:09:37,600
Oh my god!

132
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:40,233
<i> Please stop causing trouble.</i>

133
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:44,200
<i>We've already explained
this earlier.</i>

134
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,833
<i> We have a demolition order.</i>

135
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:53,400
We're asking you to cooperate,
so this doesn't turn into chaos.

136
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:56,467
Wait. We never received
any demolition notice!

137
00:09:56,600 --> 00:10:00,233
And we're still negotiating
with the landowner!

138
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:03,167
The landowner's had enough!

139
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:11,067
If you don't leave,
we'll tear these houses down!

140
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,700
You can't do this!

141
00:10:12,833 --> 00:10:15,500
Even if we don't have titles,
we've lived here for years!

142
00:10:15,633 --> 00:10:18,433
We'll fight for our rights!

143
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,267
Jobert...

144
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,067
Jobert!

145
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:50,933
- Mom. Where's my brother?
- Marj, where's your brother?

146
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,933
Jobert!

147
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,267
Jobert!

148
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,400
Jobert!

149
00:12:02,567 --> 00:12:03,800
Please have mercy!

150
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,367
Have mercy on our homes!

151
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,200
Please have mercy!

152
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:23,767
Our house!

153
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:27,633
Our house!

154
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:33,333
Jobert!

155
00:12:33,467 --> 00:12:34,967
Wait, Jobert!

156
00:12:38,733 --> 00:12:39,933
Jobert!

157
00:12:51,467 --> 00:12:52,200
Jobert!

158
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:54,500
Hey! Jobert!

159
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:55,800
Jobert!

160
00:13:02,633 --> 00:13:05,900
I'm here, it's okay.

161
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,933
I'm scared!

162
00:13:13,933 --> 00:13:18,067
The good news is, we didn't find
any fractures on Jobert.

163
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,800
His X-rays are normal.

164
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:22,600
Thank you so much, Doc.

165
00:13:22,767 --> 00:13:24,100
You're welcome.

166
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,500
Thank you, Doctor.

167
00:13:29,233 --> 00:13:31,300
Sorry, Marj.

168
00:13:31,433 --> 00:13:34,100
You worried about me.

169
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:35,833
It's okay.

170
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:38,200
What matters is you're safe.

171
00:13:41,167 --> 00:13:43,433
Let's go home.

172
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,633
Mom!

173
00:13:57,767 --> 00:13:59,167
What's wrong?

174
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,867
Marj...

175
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,600
our house is gone.

176
00:14:03,733 --> 00:14:07,067
We couldn't save
any of our things.

177
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:10,533
I don't know where
we're supposed to go, Marj.

178
00:14:14,867 --> 00:14:16,500
I don't know either, Mom.

179
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:20,067
Marj...

180
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:23,700
haven't you sold
some properties?

181
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:25,500
You earned from those, right?

182
00:14:25,633 --> 00:14:28,200
You got commissions, didn't you?

183
00:14:31,367 --> 00:14:33,333
Mom...

184
00:14:33,467 --> 00:14:35,333
I already used it.

185
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:42,167
I paid a lump sum for the house
Randall and I are building.

186
00:14:44,533 --> 00:14:49,267
I'm sorry,
I didn't know this would happen.

187
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:52,767
I'm sorry, Mom.

188
00:14:52,900 --> 00:14:54,333
What are we going to do now,
Marj?

189
00:14:54,467 --> 00:14:56,667
This is a real problem.

190
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,700
Sorry, babe.

191
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:12,967
This is all the cash
I have right now.

192
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:17,367
Our savings went into that
lump sum payment for the house.

193
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:20,667
Thank you, babe.
This helps my family a lot.

194
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:23,833
We really need it.

195
00:15:23,967 --> 00:15:27,067
Maybe we shouldn't have paid
that much for the house yet.

196
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,733
Don't think about that.
It's fine.

197
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:30,800
We've already made
the down payment.

198
00:15:30,933 --> 00:15:34,700
Once it's done, we can move in.

199
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:37,533
I'll just look
for a temporary place for us.

200
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:40,600
If you like,
you guys can stay with me.

201
00:15:40,733 --> 00:15:44,467
Babe, we won't fit
in your studio apartment.

202
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,667
And I don't want to be a burden.

203
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,333
It's okay.

204
00:15:49,467 --> 00:15:51,700
What matters is that
you have somewhere to stay.

205
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:57,133
I really appreciate everything
you're doing for us.

206
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,433
Thank you.

207
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:01,600
Don't worry...

208
00:16:01,733 --> 00:16:03,467
I'll figure something out.

209
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:17,467
Careful, okay?

210
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,067
You'll stay here.

211
00:16:35,667 --> 00:16:38,100
You should be grateful
I feel sorry for you, Marj.

212
00:16:38,233 --> 00:16:41,867
If you weren't my cousin,
I wouldn't let you stay here.

213
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:43,833
Thank you so much, Hilda.

214
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,733
Won't your brother be a problem?

215
00:16:49,867 --> 00:16:52,667
He might break things
or hurt someone.

216
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,933
Hilda, watch your mouth.

217
00:16:56,067 --> 00:16:57,533
Jobert's not like that.

218
00:16:59,033 --> 00:17:00,300
Don't worry, Hilda.

219
00:17:00,433 --> 00:17:03,467
My brother's kind
and he listens.

220
00:17:03,600 --> 00:17:05,467
Just make sure of that, okay?

221
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,733
Wow, what a miracle!
You actually came home!

222
00:17:07,867 --> 00:17:10,533
You should've just slept
at the gambling den!

223
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:12,233
So noisy!

224
00:17:13,267 --> 00:17:14,267
So noisy!

225
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:16,833
Marj, how long
can Jobert stay here

226
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,067
if she's always like that?

227
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,733
Mom, this is only temporary.

228
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:22,733
Trust me, we'll move soon.

229
00:17:22,867 --> 00:17:25,500
The house Randall and I
are building is almost done.

230
00:17:25,633 --> 00:17:27,633
- Just hang in there.
- So noisy.

231
00:17:27,767 --> 00:17:29,133
Come on, Jobert.
Let's go inside.

232
00:17:29,267 --> 00:17:30,400
Here, come on.

233
00:17:30,533 --> 00:17:32,967
Lie down and rest.

234
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,067
<i> Lito! Come out here!</i>

235
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,333
<i> Let go of me!</i>

236
00:18:00,467 --> 00:18:04,900
<i>You have no shame, Glenda!
You stole my husband!</i>

237
00:18:05,033 --> 00:18:06,733
<i> Open the door!</i>

238
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:08,067
<i>- Marj!
- Mom!</i>

239
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:11,033
<i>Go play with your brother
for now. Jobert's over there.</i>

240
00:18:11,167 --> 00:18:14,100
<i>Leave me here.
I need to face your father!</i>

241
00:18:14,233 --> 00:18:16,967
<i>Lito! Open the door!
You shameless people!</i>

242
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,967
<i> Open the door!</i>

243
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:20,233
<i> Who is that?</i>

244
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,167
Oh, it's you.

245
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,400
What's your problem now?

246
00:18:24,533 --> 00:18:27,400
You've got some nerve!
How dare you!

247
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:32,133
Sorry to tell you, your husband
is crazy about me!

248
00:18:32,267 --> 00:18:33,700
Oh, really? Crazy about you?

249
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:37,200
<i>- Let go of me!
- Mom!</i>

250
00:18:37,333 --> 00:18:40,800
<i>I'm the legal wife!
I have the right to this house!</i>

251
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:41,833
<i> Get out!</i>

252
00:18:41,967 --> 00:18:43,533
<i>- Oh, yeah?
- This house belongs to us!</i>

253
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:44,633
<i>- Lito!
- How dare you!</i>

254
00:18:44,767 --> 00:18:46,500
<i> Lito!</i>

255
00:18:46,633 --> 00:18:48,300
<i> You're shameless!</i>

256
00:18:48,433 --> 00:18:51,467
<i> Lito!</i>

257
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,533
<i> Lito!</i>

258
00:18:56,533 --> 00:18:58,933
<i> Enough, Evelyn!</i>

259
00:18:59,067 --> 00:19:01,600
<i>You don't have any rights
to this house anymore.</i>

260
00:19:01,733 --> 00:19:04,767
<i>This house is under
my siblings' and my name.</i>

261
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:09,067
<i>Even if we're still married,
you can't claim this place.</i>

262
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,633
<i> Do you understand?</i>

263
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:14,433
<i>Have mercy
on your children and me.</i>

264
00:19:14,567 --> 00:19:17,133
<i>For the sake of our kids, Lito.</i>

265
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:21,767
<i>We have nowhere to go.
Please. Have mercy on us.</i>

266
00:19:21,900 --> 00:19:24,233
<i> I don't need them!</i>

267
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:28,100
<i>They'll just get in the way
of my new family with Glenda.</i>

268
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:32,033
<i>- You can leave now.
- You heard him. Get out! Go!</i>

269
00:19:32,167 --> 00:19:33,367
<i> Leave!</i>

270
00:19:34,633 --> 00:19:35,700
<i> You're ruining the mood!</i>

271
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:38,200
<i> You're stressing us out!</i>

272
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:39,500
<i> Lito!</i>

273
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:43,433
<i> Lito!</i>

274
00:19:47,933 --> 00:19:53,500
<i>If Dad doesn't want us anymore,
let's stop forcing it, Mom.</i>

275
00:19:53,633 --> 00:19:55,567
<i> Leave him be!</i>

276
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,700
<i> This is humiliating.</i>

277
00:20:27,567 --> 00:20:29,000
Hey.

278
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:32,400
Looks like I still have
a long way to go

279
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:36,367
to hit my quota
and get that promotion.

280
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:39,167
You've got this, babe.

281
00:20:39,300 --> 00:20:42,367
You're one of the best agents
in the Batangas branch.

282
00:20:56,267 --> 00:20:58,133
Girl, you look hot!

283
00:20:58,267 --> 00:20:59,600
You're glowing.

284
00:20:59,733 --> 00:21:01,100
Of course.

285
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,833
I need to close a lot of deals
to get promoted.

286
00:21:04,967 --> 00:21:06,333
Well...

287
00:21:06,467 --> 00:21:08,133
Let's go?

288
00:21:08,300 --> 00:21:09,467
Let's go.

289
00:21:18,033 --> 00:21:20,667
So you're also vying
for the promotion, Marj?

290
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:25,333
Good luck to both of us.

291
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,067
I know you have the edge
right now

292
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:29,800
since you just won an award.

293
00:21:29,933 --> 00:21:31,733
But I love a good challenge.

294
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,000
Thanks, Thea.

295
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,867
Good luck to you, too.

296
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:42,367
Honestly, I really admire you.

297
00:21:42,533 --> 00:21:47,933
Even with those rumors
saying you only hit your quota

298
00:21:48,067 --> 00:21:51,100
because your boyfriend
gives you clients.

299
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:52,567
Hey, that's not true!

300
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:56,100
Whoever's spreading that
is just trying to ruin Marj.

301
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:57,933
I agree.

302
00:21:58,067 --> 00:22:00,233
Don't worry, Marj.

303
00:22:00,367 --> 00:22:05,100
I'm sure our boss will promote
whoever truly deserves it.

304
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:08,433
Not someone who just relies
on connections.

305
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:13,033
I can succeed on my own.

306
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:15,500
I don't need to depend
on anyone.

307
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:19,067
Oh, no!

308
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:22,133
Marj, I wasn't talking
about you!

309
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:24,367
You're getting a bit defensive.

310
00:22:27,367 --> 00:22:28,967
Anyway, I got to go.

311
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:31,800
I still have
a lot of clients waiting.

312
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:34,200
It must be nice
having so much free time.

313
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:36,767
Enjoy.

314
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:39,400
Let's go.

315
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:44,633
She's just pretending to care.

316
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:48,200
If I know, she's the one
spreading those rumors.

317
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,567
Just ignore her, Babe.

318
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:53,767
I'm not planning
to stoop to her level.

319
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:57,400
But I'll prove
I deserve that promotion.

320
00:22:57,533 --> 00:23:02,700
And for my family, I'll do
whatever it takes to beat her.

321
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:10,467
Girl! You look so fancy!

322
00:23:10,600 --> 00:23:11,933
- Well...
- Looks like you bought out

323
00:23:12,067 --> 00:23:13,000
the entire department store.

324
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:15,000
Oh, please,
this isn't even enough.

325
00:23:15,133 --> 00:23:16,433
I still want to do
retail therapy

326
00:23:16,567 --> 00:23:19,900
to get over how annoyed I am
at Marj.

327
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,133
You're so competitive.

328
00:23:22,300 --> 00:23:24,733
But seriously,
why do you even work?

329
00:23:24,867 --> 00:23:26,533
You're a Villareal.

330
00:23:26,667 --> 00:23:30,533
You don't have to struggle.
Your family's rich, right?

331
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:33,567
I don't want to be labeled
a trust-fund baby.

332
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:38,800
I want to prove
I can make it on my own.

333
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:43,333
That's why I need to close

334
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:46,933
multiple deals
with my OFW clients.

335
00:23:47,067 --> 00:23:49,233
Are they sure buyers?

336
00:23:49,367 --> 00:23:50,600
Absolutely.

337
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:52,800
I'm just waiting
for the contracts to be signed.

338
00:23:52,933 --> 00:23:57,633
Once I close them,
that promotion is guaranteed.

339
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:01,100
Let's see if Marj
can still brag after that.

340
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:05,900
Thank you again.

341
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:08,533
Buying my house
was totally hassle-free

342
00:24:08,667 --> 00:24:11,067
because of you, Marj.
Thank you so much.

343
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:14,500
I'm really happy to hear that
you're very satisfied, Ma'am.

344
00:24:14,633 --> 00:24:18,367
Here you go. Congratulations,
and enjoy your new dream house.

345
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:20,833
Sis!

346
00:24:20,967 --> 00:24:24,267
Oh, Marj, these are my coworkers
from Canada.

347
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:28,133
They're also looking to buy
a house and a lot.

348
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,933
They already talked
to an agent before,

349
00:24:31,067 --> 00:24:35,800
but after I told them how great
my experience was with you,

350
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:38,000
they want to switch to you.

351
00:24:38,133 --> 00:24:39,400
That's right.

352
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:45,067
-You're sure? You're not joking?
- Yes, yes.

353
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:49,667
Honestly, I really need this.
So the timing is perfect.

354
00:24:49,800 --> 00:24:53,000
Wait, you said they were already
talking to another agent?

355
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:54,900
Yeah. What was her name again?

356
00:24:55,033 --> 00:24:57,400
Oh, right. Miss Thea Villareal.

357
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:59,500
But she's hard to deal with.

358
00:24:59,633 --> 00:25:02,567
She doesn't really accommodate
our questions.

359
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:05,767
It feels like she's always
rushing us to sign.

360
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:07,967
I'm really sorry, Ma'am.

361
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:10,200
As much as I want
to help you,

362
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:14,867
I don't want my colleague
to think I took her clients.

363
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:18,800
Then what do we do?
We want you.

364
00:25:18,933 --> 00:25:20,967
- Yeah, that's a shame.
- If you decline,

365
00:25:21,100 --> 00:25:24,033
we won't go back
to Miss Thea anyway.

366
00:25:24,167 --> 00:25:26,767
Maybe we're just going to look
for another company.

367
00:25:28,667 --> 00:25:31,667
So, are you in or not?

368
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,567
Wait, Ma'am.

369
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,800
I thought we had an agreement?

370
00:25:43,933 --> 00:25:46,767
Why did you suddenly
change your mind?

371
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:50,100
We were referred to Ms. Castillo
by one of our colleagues.

372
00:25:50,233 --> 00:25:52,167
She has really good feedback.

373
00:25:52,300 --> 00:25:54,400
So we decided to transfer
to her.

374
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:59,000
You mean Marj Castillo?

375
00:26:02,067 --> 00:26:03,233
Ma'am,

376
00:26:03,367 --> 00:26:06,633
you should've consulted me
first before deciding.

377
00:26:06,767 --> 00:26:09,533
Marj barely has any experience.

378
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:13,000
She won't be able
to handle you properly.

379
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:15,300
Please don't take it
against her.

380
00:26:15,433 --> 00:26:18,400
We made the decision,
so it's not her fault.

381
00:26:19,467 --> 00:26:22,767
Again, we're very sorry.

382
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:24,467
Suit yourselves.

383
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:29,000
But if something goes wrong,
don't say I didn't warn you.

384
00:26:30,767 --> 00:26:33,000
Okay. Thank you very much.

385
00:26:33,133 --> 00:26:35,967
Ma'am, Ma'am, it's just...

386
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:44,900
So what about
your promotion now?

387
00:26:45,033 --> 00:26:47,133
This is all Marj's fault.

388
00:26:47,267 --> 00:26:49,333
I'm sure she stole my clients

389
00:26:49,467 --> 00:26:52,333
so she'd get promoted
instead of me.

390
00:26:53,367 --> 00:26:56,967
I'm not letting this slide.

391
00:26:57,100 --> 00:26:59,233
She messed
with the wrong person.

392
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:05,900
Babe,

393
00:27:06,033 --> 00:27:08,867
I feel guilty about Thea.

394
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:11,500
She's losing clients
because of me.

395
00:27:11,633 --> 00:27:13,400
But at the same time,

396
00:27:13,533 --> 00:27:16,467
I can't just turn down
that opportunity.

397
00:27:17,867 --> 00:27:19,567
This is for my family.

398
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:23,467
You have nothing
to feel guilty about.

399
00:27:23,600 --> 00:27:25,333
You didn't do anything wrong.

400
00:27:26,967 --> 00:27:28,733
If you and Thea
switched places,

401
00:27:28,867 --> 00:27:31,033
I'm sure she'd do
the same thing.

402
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:35,367
Okay.

403
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:38,400
I'll just talk to her
when we see each other.

404
00:27:38,533 --> 00:27:40,067
I'll explain what happened

405
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,867
so she won't take it
the wrong way.

406
00:27:45,133 --> 00:27:48,100
Marj, congrats.

407
00:27:48,233 --> 00:27:51,400
Looks like you got the clients
I worked so hard for.

408
00:27:51,567 --> 00:27:54,000
So tell me,

409
00:27:54,133 --> 00:27:57,700
how did you badmouth me to
convince them to move to you?

410
00:27:57,833 --> 00:27:59,967
Thea, I'm sorry, but...

411
00:28:00,100 --> 00:28:01,200
they were the ones
who came to me

412
00:28:01,333 --> 00:28:03,600
and insisted on transferring.

413
00:28:04,900 --> 00:28:07,133
Excuse me, Thea.

414
00:28:07,267 --> 00:28:08,600
Before you start
accusing people,

415
00:28:08,733 --> 00:28:10,533
maybe learn
the whole story first.

416
00:28:10,667 --> 00:28:11,867
I know everything already.

417
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:15,900
Your girlfriend here
is just fake-nice!

418
00:28:17,233 --> 00:28:19,067
You're unbelievable, Marj.

419
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,800
Is that really who you are?

420
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:25,200
You don't care who you step on
as long as you get ahead?

421
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:29,900
Thea, I don't need to steal
anyone's clients to succeed.

422
00:28:30,033 --> 00:28:34,167
If a client chooses to transfer,
that means there's a problem.

423
00:28:34,300 --> 00:28:35,900
Like what?

424
00:28:36,033 --> 00:28:38,333
Before you showed up,
everything was fine.

425
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:40,867
They didn't complain
to me at all.

426
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:43,267
Maybe they were just too
polite to say it to your face.

427
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:44,967
Because they told me themselves

428
00:28:45,100 --> 00:28:47,133
that they weren't happy
with you.

429
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:49,767
Stop pretending
to be innocent, Marj.

430
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:52,333
Just admit you did it
on purpose.

431
00:28:52,467 --> 00:28:54,800
Remember this, Marj.

432
00:28:54,933 --> 00:28:58,100
You started this, not me.

433
00:28:58,267 --> 00:29:00,967
Now you're going to see
the real Thea.

434
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:04,133
You're going to regret
messing with me.

435
00:29:19,333 --> 00:29:20,300
Babe,

436
00:29:22,033 --> 00:29:24,833
I'm scared of Thea's threat.

437
00:29:24,967 --> 00:29:28,767
What if she's really planning
something bad against me?

438
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:30,500
Babe, don't be scared.

439
00:29:30,667 --> 00:29:32,233
I'll protect you.

440
00:29:34,467 --> 00:29:36,167
Thea can't do whatever
she's saying.

441
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:38,633
If she wants a fight,
she'll have to deal with me.

442
00:29:38,767 --> 00:29:40,433
Thank you, babe.

443
00:29:41,767 --> 00:29:45,533
I feel so blessed
to have you as my boyfriend.

444
00:29:45,667 --> 00:29:49,233
I know I can count on you,
and that you love me.

445
00:29:50,700 --> 00:29:52,467
You know,

446
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:56,233
at first I was really scared
to say yes to you.

447
00:29:56,367 --> 00:30:00,567
What happened to my parents
really traumatized me.

448
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:04,100
But as time went by,

449
00:30:04,267 --> 00:30:05,833
you proved to me

450
00:30:05,967 --> 00:30:09,600
that you're someone I can trust
and that you'd never hurt me.

451
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:15,300
Babe?

452
00:30:15,433 --> 00:30:17,767
Did I say something wrong?

453
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:19,600
No, babe.

454
00:30:19,733 --> 00:30:23,167
I'm just really happy to hear
all your compliments.

455
00:30:23,300 --> 00:30:24,600
Thank you.

456
00:30:33,933 --> 00:30:35,900
Wait a second, okay?
My cousin's calling.

457
00:30:36,067 --> 00:30:37,267
Sure.

458
00:30:43,967 --> 00:30:46,167
Babe,
there's a family emergency.

459
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:47,667
I need to go home to Laguna.

460
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:49,833
Okay, okay. Go ahead.

461
00:30:49,967 --> 00:30:51,067
I'll just take a taxi.

462
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,700
- Are you sure you'll be okay?
- Yeah, I'll be fine.

463
00:30:53,833 --> 00:30:55,533
Let's talk later.

464
00:30:57,633 --> 00:30:58,900
Take care.

465
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:04,733
That Marj really
has some nerve!

466
00:31:04,867 --> 00:31:06,667
She steals my clients

467
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,367
and then plays innocent
as if she did nothing.

468
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:09,967
So annoying!

469
00:31:10,133 --> 00:31:11,000
If it were up to me,

470
00:31:11,133 --> 00:31:13,733
I'd pull that witch's hair
so we'd be even.

471
00:31:13,867 --> 00:31:15,767
Hair-pulling isn't enough.

472
00:31:15,900 --> 00:31:18,100
Because of her,
I lost my commission.

473
00:31:18,233 --> 00:31:21,500
And now my promotion
is basically gone!

474
00:31:21,633 --> 00:31:25,433
That woman deserves way
worse than just that.

475
00:31:25,567 --> 00:31:27,333
So what are you planning to do?

476
00:31:33,633 --> 00:31:34,733
Is that Randall?

477
00:31:39,767 --> 00:31:41,833
Maybe he and Marj
are just out eating.

478
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:45,700
Let's follow them.

479
00:31:45,833 --> 00:31:47,900
They ruined my day,

480
00:31:48,033 --> 00:31:50,733
so I'll make sure theirs gets
ruined, too.

481
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:29,933
Yes?

482
00:32:31,367 --> 00:32:32,933
I'm Thea.

483
00:32:33,067 --> 00:32:35,000
I work with Randall.

484
00:32:35,133 --> 00:32:36,567
Oh, he's not here.

485
00:32:36,700 --> 00:32:38,467
Do you need something from him?

486
00:32:39,433 --> 00:32:43,467
Actually, you're the one
I want to talk to.

487
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:44,933
About what?

488
00:32:53,033 --> 00:32:56,933
Hello, Ma'am.
Welcome to our open house.

489
00:32:57,067 --> 00:32:58,200
You can help yourself
to some snacks for now.

490
00:32:58,333 --> 00:33:00,367
We're just waiting
for the others.

491
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:02,733
Are you Marj Castillo?

492
00:33:02,867 --> 00:33:04,267
Yes, I am.

493
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:06,433
How did you know my name?

494
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:08,833
I've heard a lot about you.

495
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,867
All right, I guess we can
start the tour now.

496
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,100
Wait. Wait!

497
00:33:17,233 --> 00:33:18,900
Sorry for the trouble, Randall.

498
00:33:19,033 --> 00:33:21,700
Jobert's been cranky
for a while.

499
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:23,467
He really wanted to see
his sister.

500
00:33:23,633 --> 00:33:24,767
It's okay, Auntie.

501
00:33:27,567 --> 00:33:29,367
Thank you, Randall.

502
00:33:29,500 --> 00:33:32,467
Excuse me, Ma'am.
I'm here to work.

503
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:35,333
Please take your personal
issues somewhere else.

504
00:33:35,467 --> 00:33:37,200
I have nothing to do with that.

505
00:33:37,333 --> 00:33:39,833
- Marj, babe, here's Jobert.
- There's your sister, Jobert.

506
00:33:39,967 --> 00:33:42,933
Babe? Wow.

507
00:33:44,067 --> 00:33:46,933
That's a pretty sweet
nickname, Randall.

508
00:33:48,900 --> 00:33:51,400
Randall, do you know her?

509
00:33:51,533 --> 00:33:55,233
I just happen to be
this man's wife.

510
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:59,733
And the mother of his children!

511
00:33:59,867 --> 00:34:02,567
So you should be ashamed
of yourself.

512
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:05,200
You're destroying our family!

513
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:17,900
Those OFW clients decided
not to buy anymore.

514
00:34:18,033 --> 00:34:21,600
They got turned off by the
agent they were dealing with.

515
00:34:21,733 --> 00:34:25,000
The real issue here is the
alleged illicit affair.

516
00:34:25,133 --> 00:34:28,233
They're saying she got
involved with a married man.

517
00:34:28,367 --> 00:34:29,833
You lied to me,
you bastard!

518
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,067
Everything I felt for you
was real!

519
00:34:32,200 --> 00:34:33,233
Lies!

520
00:34:33,367 --> 00:34:36,667
There's a reason
I really want to do this.

521
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,867
There's a lot you still
don't know about this house.

522
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,000
The Torrecampos
have many secrets.

523
00:34:41,133 --> 00:34:43,167
Watch what you say, Edward.

524
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:44,500
Don't embarrass our family.

525
00:34:44,633 --> 00:34:47,167
It's fine. Everyone's willing to
wait for the golden boy anyway.

526
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:48,200
No, thank you.

527
00:34:48,333 --> 00:34:49,667
It's all on video.
You can see it clearly.

528
00:34:49,800 --> 00:34:51,800
She's a mistress
and a troublemaker.

529
00:34:51,933 --> 00:34:54,600
Pervert! Don't interfere,
or I'll slap you!

530
00:34:54,733 --> 00:34:56,467
Next time
you do something to me,

531
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:59,200
I'll do something even worse
to you.
